The paper presents a new deep learning architecture for supervised learning with sparse and irregularly sampled multivariate time series. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, since the paper focuses on the development of a new deep learning architecture, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of physiological time series data in electronic health records also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SI. The potential application of the proposed architecture to computer vision tasks could also justify the inclusion of cs.CV and cs.NE as likely sub-categories.
